RNA-seq.tooltip: 3' Bias statistics (25th percentile): These aggregate statistics are based on the total coverage in 100 bp windows on both the 3' and 5' ends of a gene. The windows are both offset 150 bases into the gene. This computation is only performed on genes at least 600bp long and with at least 5 unambiguous reads. A gene with even coverage in both it's 3' and 5' windows would have a bias of 0.5; bias near 1 or 0 may indicate degradation

3' Bias statistics (75th percentile): These aggregate statistics are based on the total coverage in 100 bp windows on both the 3' and 5' ends of a gene. A gene with even coverage in both it's 3' and 5' windows would have a bias of 0.5; bias near 1 or 0 may indicate degradation
